hopobject.body: I hate shopping candida viagra He believes a sense of humour is a prerequisite for spin bowlers. Theirs is a dark art in which dexterity and mind games are combined with turn, flight and drift to outwit batsmen. Swann’s ability to put more revolutions on the ball means he can excel in diverse pitch conditions but, without the defence of raw pace, on a bad day a spin bowler can be humiliated. 'You need guile, skill and luck, but you have got to be able to laugh at yourself otherwise you will be suicidal every other day,’ he says.
